                <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/376">
                  <persName xml:lang="en">Basil of Caesarea</persName>
                </author>
                <title xml:lang="en">The first discourse on Faith</title>
                <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܡܐܡܪܐ. ܩܕܡܝܐ. ܕܥܠ ܗܝܡܢܘܬܐ<locus from="44a"/>
                </rubric>
                <note>See 
                  <bibl>Opera, Paris, 1839, t. ii. p. 182<ref target="smblBibl474"/>
                  </bibl>; 
                  <bibl>Migne, Patrol. Gr., t. xxxi., col. 463<ref target="smblBibl475"/>
                  </bibl>.
                </note>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="b4" n="8">
                <locus from="46b" to="48b">Foll. 46b-48b</locus>
                <author ref="http://syriaca.org/person/376">
                  <persName xml:lang="en">Basil of Caesarea</persName>
                </author>
                <title xml:lang="en">The second discourse on Faith</title>
                <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܡܐܡܪܐ. ܕܬܪ̈ܝܢ. ܕܥܠ. ܗܝܡܢܘܬܐ.<locus from="46b"/>
                </rubric>
                <note>Slightly imperfect at the end.</note>                
                <note>See 
                  <bibl>Opera, Paris, 1839, t. ii. p. 867<ref target="smblBibl474"/>
                  </bibl>; 
                  <bibl>Migne, Patrol. Gr., t. xxxi., col. 1487<ref target="smblBibl475"/>
                  </bibl>.
                </note>
              </msItem>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 12 3/8 in. by 9 5/8, consisting of 49 leaves, all of which are more or less stained with oil, <locus from="12" to="12">12,</locus>
              <locus from="13" to="13">13</locus>, and <locus from="41" to="44">41—44</locus>. The original signatures of the quires are no longer apparent. The volume is imperfect both at the beginning and the end. Each page is divided into two columns, of from 40 to 48 lines. </p>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
              <supportDesc material="perg">
                <support>
                  <material>Vellum</material>
                </support>
                <extent>
                  <measure type="composition" unit="leaf" quantity="49">49 ff.</measure>
                  <dimensions type="leaf" unit="inch">
                    <height quantity="12.375">12 3/8</height>
                    <width quantity="9.625">9 5/8</width>
                  </dimensions>
                </extent>
                <collation>
                  <p>The original signatures of the quires are no longer apparent.</p>
                </collation>
                <condition>
                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>All of the leaves are more or less stained with oil.</p>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                      <p>Some of the leaves are much torn, especially foll.<locus from="1">1</locus>, <locus from="12">12</locus>, <locus from="13">13</locus>, and <locus from="41" to="44">41—44</locus>.</p>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </condition>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout columns="2" writtenLines="40 48">
                  <p>Each page is divided into two columns, of from 40 to 48 lines.</p>
                </layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="2">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr-Syre" medium="unknown">
                It is written in a small, regular, elegant Esṭrangělā, probably of the <date notBefore="0400" notAfter="0500" calendar="Gregorian">vth</date> cent.
              </handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote2" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                See additions.
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <additions>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <locus from="49"/>
                  <ref target="#handNote2"/>
                  <p>Whether fol. 49 really belongs to this volume is doubtful; it is so much stained and soiled, that the writing upon it is no longer legible.</p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
            </physDesc>
